<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="Trim" class="currentChild" href="Trim">Trim</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
To cut away a small portion of an edge of a stack of sheets or a <a title="Book Block" href="Book_Block">book block</a>, either to reduce a set of sheets to a desired size or to cut away <a title="Signature" href="Signature">signature</a> folds. See <a title="Cutting and Trimming" href="Cutting_and_Trimming">Cutting and Trimming</a>. It is also used as a noun to refer to the <a title="Trim Size" href="Trim_Size">trim size</a>. 
</p>
<p id="l3">
In graphics, <em>trim</em> means to cut away a portion of a line, arc, or circle. 
</p>
<p id="l5">
In video production, <em>trim</em> means to select specific frames for inclusion in a master tape. 
</p>
<p id="l7">
Also a term to describe a shorter version of preventative maintenance on a printer. It is also a term used to cut the tractor feed portion from continuous forms. 
</p>
